  "text": "The results of this study represent a signifi cant advance in addressing an unmet need in the treatment of HCC. All previous second-line trials of novel agents have failed; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] thus no eff ective systemic therapies after progression on sorafenib are currently available. These data underscore that prolonging exposure to multikinase inhibitors such as the sequence of sorafenib and regorafenib in conjunction with proper management of adverse events can lead to an extension in survival. In conclusion, this study met its primary endpoint showing that regorafenib improves overall survival in patients with HCC who had disease progression during fi rst-line treatment with sorafenib.",
